      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022R2) is a commercially validated code with documented QA procedures, version control, and regression test suite. Software quality assurance requirements for MRL 2 are satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Numerical code verification confirmed through method of manufactured solutions applied to the governing Navier-Stokes equations. Observed order of convergence matches theoretical order, confirming correct implementation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study performed across three mesh densities (3.2M, 8.7M, and 22.1M elements). Richardson extrapolation yields discretization error below 4% for hemolysis index, satisfying MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions from FDA benchmark dataset are well-documented with controlled fluid properties (bovine blood analog), pump speed, and flow rate. Test conditions adequately represent the simulation inputs at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
